# Fluff Date: 2026-02-24 14:22:50
<overview>
<p>The Fredasa-class corvette is the smallest warship design produced by the Clans, developed during the mid-thirtieth century as a fast raider and picket vessel. Named for Ikolor Fredasa, the Commanding General of the Star League Defense Force from 2707 to 2729 and a controversial figure known as the Father of the Military Renaissance, the class emerged alongside comparable small vessels such as the Corone and Molniya but outlasted both to remain in active Clan service through Operation Revival and beyond. Inner Sphere naval officers classify the Fredasa as a raider rather than a true corvette, reflecting its primary tactical role of fast strikes against vulnerable targets rather than sustained fleet engagements. The design's combination of high acceleration, low emergence signature, and a lithium-fusion battery make it exceptionally well suited for hit-and-run operations deep behind enemy lines.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At just 180,000 tons, the Fredasa achieved remarkable speed for a warship, reaching a safe acceleration of five thrust points with a maximum of eight, enabling short bursts of four gravities. This exceptional agility was achieved through distinctive downward-thrust domes suspended below the hull, giving the vessel superlative maneuverability for its displacement class. The hull carried 131.5 tons of Valiant Lamellor ferro-carbide armor, lighter than comparable Inner Sphere corvettes but superior to Star League-era vessels of similar size. A lithium-fusion battery supplemented the compact Kearny-Fuchida drive, allowing consecutive jumps without recharging.</p><p>The weapons suite mixed capital and conventional systems for versatility. A single NAC/40 naval autocannon dominated the nose alongside two NL45 naval lasers and two Gauss rifles for forward-arc firepower. Four NAC/10 naval autocannons covered the fore quarter arcs, while additional NL45 batteries protected the broadsides and aft. Anti-fighter defense combined sixteen ER Large Lasers, sixteen ER Small Lasers, six Streak SRM-6 launchers, and four LRM-20 launchers with Artemis IV fire control systems. A single docking collar and twenty OmniFighter bays provided limited transport capacity suited to the raider mission profile.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The CGB Black Ghost served in Clan Ghost Bear's flexible naval reserve and was destroyed at the Second Naval Battle of Alshain in May 3067 alongside its Nova Cat counterpart SLS Spirit Sight, both lost during the catastrophic Trial of Retribution. The CIH Swift Bait was captured by Clan Jade Falcon during Operation ICE STORM in 3071 and rechristened Jade Tornado, remaining in Falcon service into the Dark Age. Its sister ship CIH Whelp was destroyed in the Dark Nebula in March 3072 after gutting an enemy assault DropShip wave but suffering fatal armor breaches. The CDS Swift Strike survived a three-year misjump ordeal beginning in 3073, losing over half its crew before returning to civilization in November 3077, and was later transferred to Clan Snow Raven as the Kutkh. The CSA Arcadian Asp and CSA Vicious Fang participated in Star Adder Watch operations during the Wars of Reaving, including orbital bombardment of Dark Caste positions at Ghent, and remained among only thirteen operational Star Adder warships as of 3085.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Fredasa entered service around 2962, during a period when several Clans were developing small warship designs to supplement their aging fleets of Star League-era vessels. Approximately sixteen examples were constructed across multiple Clans, with the design seeing widespread adoption among both Warden and Crusader factions. By the time of the Clan Invasion in 3049, the Fredasa was the only small Clan-designed warship class still in active service, with examples serving in the naval forces of Clans Ghost Bear, Nova Cat, Steel Viper, Ice Hellion, Star Adder, Cloud Cobra, Diamond Shark, Snow Raven, Jade Falcon, and Smoke Jaguar.</p><p>The class earned a dramatic early distinction when the Blue Star Irregulars mercenary unit captured a Jade Falcon Fredasa at Quarell in 3055, ignoring batchall protocols and ramming the vessel with a damaged JumpShip to disable its command center. Wolf's Dragoons subsequently repaired and partially refitted the vessel, which served the Irregulars as the Kerensky's Blues until its destruction at Black Earth in January 3069 while protecting fleeing civilian refugees from Jade Falcon pursuit.</p><p>The Wars of Reaving proved devastating for the class. The Second Naval Battle of Alshain in May 3067 claimed two Fredasa corvettes when Clan Nova Cat challenged Clan Ghost Bear in a catastrophic Trial of Retribution, destroying half the Ghost Bear fleet alongside comparable Nova Cat losses. Additional vessels were lost during Clan Steel Viper's aggressive campaigns at Lum, the Clan Cloud Cobra losses during the Trial of Annihilation at Circe, and the destruction of Ice Hellion forces during their failed invasion of the Jade Falcon Occupation Zone. The Diamond Shark vessel Swift Strike endured a particularly harrowing ordeal, suffering a misjump while fleeing a Star Adder blockade at York in 3073 and spending three years stranded in an unknown system while over half its crew perished performing emergency repairs.</p><p>By the ilClan era, the Fredasa remained in limited service. The surviving Diamond Shark vessel was transferred to Clan Snow Raven around 3091 as the Kutkh, while a captured Ice Hellion hull served Clan Jade Falcon as the Jade Tornado. Star Adder retained two operational examples in the Homeworlds. The class legacy stretched across nearly two centuries of continuous Clan service, an exceptional record for a design of such modest displacement.</p>
</history>

